{"id": "1466405796433756407", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "type": 0, "author_id": "857488861902929940", "author_name": "ersetzung", "author_bot": false, "content": "hello! I'm currently studying morimens carefully and after the first chapter I have some questions: \n\n1. Does everyone living in Morimens have silver core? So Sarah and some random passerby on the street have the same core that Aigis left behind?\n\n2. Does every awakened one have to be linked to a keeper? I don't mean just the main character, because there have been many other keeper in the history of Mythag, as I understand it. An awakened person cannot exist by himself without a link?\n\n3. What is the difference between investigator and keepers? the investigator can simply purify the dissolution, and the keeper, as I understand it, already linked himself with the awakened? or am I wrong?", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T12:13:06.372000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2026-01-29T12:13:37.470000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1466407718599393362", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "type": 0, "author_id": "753599669241643118", "author_name": "rebussohal", "author_bot": false, "content": "Not the greatest lore nerd but\n1. Nope, having a proper silver core is kind of rare. Some people do have silver bits but a full usable core is defintely not common.\n2. They can exist without a link but bad things happen. They can link to normal people though but it seems harmful to the person.\n3. As I understand it pretty much. Investigators are mythags high ranked people that have been issued a silver key but are not necessarily linked to an awakener.", "timestamp": "2026-01-29T12:20:44.652000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2026-01-29T12:21:24.343000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}, {"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
